tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within or close to normal limits, except for mild leukopenia (slightly low white blood cells) and a markedly elevated platelet distribution width, which may indicate increased platelet size variability. No acute abnormalities are evident. Mild leukopenia may warrant monitoring, especially if there are clinical symptoms or risk factors for infection. Overall, results are stable.
